72
00:06:31,990 --> 00:06:34,010
What am I going to do with him?

73
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:35,890
He'd make a very handsome throw rug.

74
00:06:35,930 --> 00:06:37,020
Zazu!

75
00:06:37,060 --> 00:06:39,500
And just think, whenever he gets dirty...

76
00:06:39,530 --> 00:06:41,860
you could take him out and beat him.

77
00:07:25,710 --> 00:07:27,370
Simba.

78
00:07:39,530 --> 00:07:41,220
Dad! Dad!

79
00:07:41,260 --> 00:07:44,720
Come on, Dad, we gotta go! Wake up!

80
00:07:44,760 --> 00:07:46,160
Sorry.

81
00:07:47,530 --> 00:07:49,530
Dad. Dad.

82
00:07:49,570 --> 00:07:52,870
Your son is awake.

83
00:07:52,910 --> 00:07:55,640
Before sunrise, he's your son.

84
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:57,700
Dad! Come on, Dad.

85
00:08:02,050 --> 00:08:04,070
You promised.

86
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:08,140
- OK, OK. I'm up, I'm up. - Yeah!

87
00:08:23,670 --> 00:08:24,970
Look, Simba.

88
00:08:25,010 --> 00:08:29,270
Everything the light touches is our kingdom.

89
00:08:29,310 --> 00:08:31,110
Wow.

90
00:08:31,150 --> 00:08:36,050
A king's time as ruler rises and falls like the sun.

91
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:40,450
One day, Simba, the sun will set on my time here...

92
00:08:40,490 --> 00:08:43,620
and will rise with you as the new king.

93
00:08:43,660 --> 00:08:46,350
- And this'll all be mine? - Everything.

94
00:08:46,390 --> 00:08:49,690
Everything the light touches.

95
00:08:49,730 --> 00:08:51,990
What about that shadowy place?

96
00:08:52,030 --> 00:08:55,330
That's beyond our borders. You must never go there, Simba.

97
00:08:55,370 --> 00:08:57,390
But I thought a king can do whatever he wants.

98
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:59,200
There's more to being king...

99
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:01,000
than getting your way all the time.

100
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:03,240
- There's more? - Simba...

101
00:09:05,110 --> 00:09:07,780
Everything you see exists together...

102
00:09:07,820 --> 00:09:09,550
in a delicate balance.

103
00:09:09,580 --> 00:09:12,580
As king, you need to understand that balance...

104
00:09:12,620 --> 00:09:14,350
and respect all the creatures...

105
00:09:14,390 --> 00:09:17,590
from the crawling ant to the leaping antelope.

106
00:09:17,630 --> 00:09:19,590
But, Dad, don't we eat the antelope?

107
00:09:19,630 --> 00:09:22,190
Yes, Simba, but let me explain.

108
00:09:22,230 --> 00:09:25,130
When we die, our bodies become the grass...

109
00:09:25,170 --> 00:09:27,730
and the antelope eat the grass.

110
00:09:27,770 --> 00:09:33,400
And so we are all connected in the great circle of life.

111
